    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The culture and style of the ancient Venetii, people of northeastern Italy who arrived about 1000 BCE and occupied an area stretching south to the Po river and west to the Vero river. This culture is unrelated to the ancient Celto-Venetic culture of Britanny.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
